title: Weisi Chen
text:
Welcome to my personal website!
Born and raised in Hangzhou, China, I moved to Sydney, Australia in 2015 to pursue university studies. I am a highly disciplined and hard-working individual with a strong passion for programming, data analysis, data visualization, and statistical modeling. With a background in pharmacy and health data science, I am interested in population-level analysis using linked data. My expertise lies in uncovering meaningful insights from complex datasets, driven by a commitment to improving health outcomes. I thrive on tackling challenging problems with analytical precision and creativity, always striving to deliver impactful results in every project I undertake.
I am currently a data analyst working at the university of New South Wales (UNSW) in Sydney, Australia. In my free time, I enjoy reading, photography, exploring cities on foot, traveling, learning/trying new things and cherishing moments with family and friends.
